2(n+2)\le(n+2)^2
P(0): 2(0 + 2) \le (0 + 2)^2 = 4 \le 4
P(n): 2(n+2)\le(n+2)^2
\begin{align}2((n + 1) + 2) &= 2((n + 2) + 1) \\ &= 2(n + 2) + 2 \\ &\le (n + 2)^2 + 2 \\ & \le n^2 + 4n + 6 \\ & \le n^2 + 6n + 9 \tag 5\\ & = ((n+1)+2)^2\end{align}
